parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wipers can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Wipers stop working
wipers stick to the windshield
wipers do not return to their normal position
wipers have a delayed return to their normal position
wipers have a sudden loss of pressure
vehicle is unable to clear snow or water from the windshield.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The hazy rear windows can cause reduced visibility, leading to accidents or making it difficult to see out of the vehicle.
symptoms: Rear windows appear cloudy
hazy
or foggy
especially in direct sunlight
making it difficult to see out of the windows
blind spots are obscured.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof or windshield can cause injuries or accidents.
symptoms: Sunroof exploded without impact
crack occurred on the windshield without road debris
windshield wipers struck the metal frame and seized.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of acceleration can cause accidents, especially when driving in traffic, and can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power while driving
often without warning
and may not respond to accelerator pedal input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked or hazy windshields and windows can obstruct the driver's view, leading to accidents, and can also cause injuries from shattered glass.
symptoms: Windshields and windows crack or shatter without incident
or appear hazy
foggy
or cloudy
reducing visibility.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unreliable brake performance can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving in heavy traffic or emergency situations.
symptoms: The brake pedal vibrates or feels soft
and the vehicle may not slow down or stop as expected
even when the brake pedal is pressed firmly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving in heavy traffic or emergency situations.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system fails
causing issues with the seat
doors
or dash display
and may not respond to user input.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Delays or failures in addressing safety recalls can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, and can lead to frustration and mistrust among vehicle owners.
symptoms: Dealerships may not have the necessary parts or expertise to address safety recalls
leading to delays or failed repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving on highways or in snowy/icy conditions, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or loses power
often in "snow mode" or when driving on snowy/icy roads
the engine RPMs surge or drop suddenly
the vehicle hesitates or jerks when accelerating
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may not respond to acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the transmission slips or fails to engage
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
and the check engine light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The powertrain recall issues can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or stall, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle is subject to a powertrain recall
but the necessary parts are not available
the vehicle has not been repaired despite notification of the recall
and the manufacturer has exceeded a reasonable amount of time for the recall repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine misfire or loss of power can cause accidents, especially when driving on highways or in snowy/icy conditions, and can lead to a loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The engine misfires or loses power
often when driving on highways or in snowy/icy conditions
the check engine light comes on
and the vehicle may not respond to acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The spontaneous explosion of the sunroof can cause injury or damage to the vehicle and its occupants.
symptoms: The sunroof explodes suddenly
often without warning
and can cause damage to the vehicle and its occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to shut off while driving, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the dashboard and radio turn off
the check-ESC message appears
and the vehicle cannot be restarted.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The battery drain issues can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leaving the driver stranded and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The battery is completely drained
the vehicle will not start
and the battery warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of sensors can cause the vehicle's safety features to malfunction, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The parking distance warning system and ultrasonic sensor error messages appear
and the sensors are clean and not blocked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the infotainment system can cause the driver to lose access to important safety features and vehicle functions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The infotainment system will not turn on
the digital instrument display is not functioning
and the safety functions are not accessible.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Blue Link and SOS Emergency Button Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Blue Link and SOS emergency button can cause the driver to be unable to access emergency services in the event of an accident or medical emergency.
symptoms: The Blue Link button and SOS emergency button do not work
and the driver is unable to connect to emergency services.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the transmission and stop idle function can cause the vehicle to lurch and make loud clunking noises, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission shifts erratically
the vehicle lurches and makes loud clunking noises
and the stop idle function does not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door and locking system can cause the driver to be unable to lock the doors, increasing the risk of theft or accidents.
symptoms: The passenger door shows as open
the door will not lock
and the door open alert sounds while driving.
